    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9b95ed8b_84c422cf",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/baserun.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 62,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-11T07:26:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "initClients does not have access to Params. My options were to:\n- pipe Params down to initClients\n- keep a pointer to the Params in baseCommandRun struct\n- overload the host flag to by default have something like \"DEFAULT:\u003cactual default\u003e\" s.t. initClients can decide whether it needs to apply the luci context hostname, when there\u0027s a DEFAULT: prefix in the flag, or strip it if no host name in the context.\n- hijack the flag registration to save only the hardcoded default to the baseCommandRun struct.\n\nThe first two were hacky because Params IIUC is intended only to initialize the struct, not to actually run the commands.\nThe third one was hacky because it\u0027s an unexpected use of the flag. Even though this option does not require adding fields to the baseCommandRun struct.\nThe fourth one is hacky because copying the hardcoded default to the baseCommandRun struct is not strictly \u0027registering\u0027 a flag.\n\nI thought 4th option was less ugly than the others. Do you have any suggestions?",
      "parentUuid": "597dba7a_1ab9d39b",
      "revId": "be5935fe9b1b6d0954f734b8fdeeaff061055054",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
