      "message": "i see. this makes sense.\n\ni think either [-include and -exclude] or [-add and -remove] to use correct opposites.\n\ni personally favor -add/remove because they are shorter and to avoid confusion with \"include into includedInvocations\" (overload of \"include\" meaning)\n\nconsider https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/common/flag#StringSlice to represent multiple invocation ids in one flag value",
